  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n /kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nCurrently, the ScaleIO Kubernetes volume plugin has a dependency on a local binary `drv_cfg` to be accessible so it can do a device map.  This dependency makes it hard to containerize the kubelet in a production environment.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nAbility to wrap kubelet binary into a container.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nDue to this dependency, containerized kubelets must launch with local paths available inside the container.\r\n",
